## 1. What the arc set out to build

A **read-and-report audit of the entire substrate** — explicitly not a build. The Codex brief (`Build_Docs/Agent_tasks/codex_task050_substrate_layer_audit.md`, read in full) opens by declaring it a "read-and-report task. Do not modify source code. Do not implement new modules. Do not refactor existing modules. The deliverables are audit reports only" (L11). Its stated rationale (L17): *"Before further consumer-layer work proceeds, the project needs an honest map of what currently exists, where each module sits in the substrate layering, and which parent primitives are missing or misplaced."* (high)

The brief pre-registered a five-phase methodology (L72-129) and five named deliverables (L172-235), all to land under `Build_Docs/Reports/task050/`:

1. **`module_layer_mapping.md`** — every `src/lloyd_v4/` module + every `scratch/` prototype placed in the L0/L1/L2/L3/L4+/Unclear hierarchy, with explicit evidence per placement.
2. **`parent_primitive_gaps.md`** — every primitive that L2+ consumers compose against but that does not exist at the correct parent layer, each classified by `SUBSTRATE_CONSTRUCTION.md §5.1` failure mode (Mode 1 not-atomic / Mode 2 two-operations-one-name / Mode 3 parent-layer-incomplete).
3. **`drift_inventory.md`** — DRY violations, misplaced modules, composition violations, hidden guard rails (Axiom 3), Axiom 11 violations, Axiom 10 violations; each with severity (B blocks-transplant / Q quality / I informational).
4. **`transplantation_readiness.md`** — scratch prototypes rated against the `§4` dissection gate; an *ordered list of the first three transplantation tasks* with capability-spread reasoning (`§6`).
5. **`task050_summary.md`** — executive summary, honest about uncertainty.

Explicit Non-Goals (brief L237-253): do not propose API designs, do not draft pre-regs, do not run pytest, do not modify any source/scratch/architecture file. The brief frames the audit as "the precursor to the first real transplantation work. Its outputs determine the order of subsequent tasks" (L26). (high)

This sits squarely inside Claude Code's authorized "Investigation / Documentation" role (CLAUDE.md §3) — no substrate authorship intended. (high)

